sentences: Evelyn Faltis was born in Trautenau, Bohemia, in 1887, the second of three daughters of Carl Johann and Maria Anna Cecilia Magdalena Faltis (born Wiesenburg) who were Viennese bourgeoisie.
After completing her studies she moved to Berlin, but settled in Vienna in 1933.
She became the first woman coach at Bayreuth and worked as accompanist at the Nuremberg Stadttheater am Ring and the Darmstadt Hoftheater, and after 1924 at the Berlin Städtische Oper.
Sonata in B minor for piano (no Op., about 1909)
Seven Songs for Voice and Piano, Op. 8 (1921)
